{
  "stem": "1857.4",
  "chunk_idx": 9,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 350.6,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "But there was a strike going on.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "So they sent us to Bremen, but we couldn't leave for United States, because the ships weren't going.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "So I spent days and evenings, just playing bridge, every single day, with some people.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "And finally, we got on a ship, end of December.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "It was-- the ship was called which arrived January 13 in New York Harbor.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] I was very sick on the ship.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "On the fourth day, I got so sick that I was-- I thought I was dying.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "And we got into a-- we called it an SOS, because we-- we landed in Halifax, Canada.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "It was such a rough voyage.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 29,
      "text": "And HIAS took us into their quarters.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 30,
      "text": "They had an office downtown New York.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 31,
      "text": "And that's where we slept-- in the HIAS office.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 32,
      "text": "I had an uncle in Chicago who sent the papers for us.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And as I was leaving the pier, a man from Krakow was standing and waiting at the pier for somebody else who was on the-- on the ship.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And he was a young doctor from Krakow whom I knew well.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And I asked him, 'Sam, who is here among other people?' And he says, this one, that one. 'And Rena is here.' I said, 'You have her phone number?' He says, 'They don't have a phone, but I give you the phone number of her uncle.' And the first thing I came to HIAS, I called, and she came over.",
      "word_count": 60
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And two days later, I left for Chicago.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "We started corresponding.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "The arrival in Chicago was really funny, because my uncle was one hell of a nice man, a terrific man.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "But he had a son who was a sickly-- sickly one.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Was a couple of years older than I was.",
      "word_count": 9
    }
  ],
